# --- Non-redistributable assets: roms/ and disks/ (directories kept, content ignored) ---
# Per owner request: keep the roms/ and disks/ directory scaffolding tracked (via
# .gitkeep) but do NOT track their content -- the .rom/.dsk binaries and MSX-DOS
# disk trees are non-redistributable and are provisioned locally, not from git.
# roms/README.md (folder documentation, human-authored) stays tracked explicitly.
/roms/*
!/roms/.gitkeep
!/roms/README.md
/disks/*
!/disks/.gitkeep

# Local game library at the repo root (user-provisioned game disks/roms, e.g.
# games/disks/<title>/*.dsk). Same non-redistributable, never-tracked policy as
# disks/ and roms/ -- provisioned locally, never committed or pushed.
/games/

# --- Editor / IDE / OS cruft ---
.vs/
*.user
.idea/
.vscode/*.log
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.DS_Store

# NOTE: bios/, roms/, and disks/ contain third-party assets (Sony HB-F1XV BIOS
# ROMs, cartridge ROMs, MSX-DOS disks) that remain their rights holders' property;
# this project asserts NO redistribution rights and makes no provenance claim.
# Per DEC-0047 the repository OWNER has made an informed decision to host the full
# repo -- bios/ included -- on a PUBLIC remote (github.com/patrick-shim/msx-2p-hbf1xv).
# bios/ stays fully tracked and is published per the owner's instruction. roms/ and
# disks/ CONTENT is untracked (provisioned locally, not from git); only the directory
# scaffolding (.gitkeep) and roms/README.md are tracked -- see the roms//disks/ block
# above. Those roms/disks binaries nonetheless remain in PRE-b5efd29 history and are
# published by any push; purging them would require history rewriting, not untracking.
# The public-exposure risk is the owner's accepted responsibility (DEC-0047).
#
# DEC-0047 supersedes DEC-0044's lean-export scope AND the private-mirror intent
# formerly annotated here as "DEC-0046" (which was never a recorded decision). The
# whole repository is the single source of truth (references/, tests/, tools/, docs/,
# debug/, .claude/ tracked normally, no `git add -f` friction). The pattern-based
# /debug/**/* ignores above still apply (regenerable runtime captures stay untracked;
# committed evidence keeps its explicit `!` exceptions).

# --- Local-only development apparatus (owner request, 2026-07-10) ---
# These directories stay fully present and usable on the LOCAL filesystem but are
# untracked so they no longer publish to the public remote. They leave the remote
# tip on the next push (prior history still contains them). NOTE: the build
# references tests/ (CMakeLists add_subdirectory(tests)), so a fresh clone lacking
# these will not configure -- the local working tree is unaffected.
/.claude/
/agent-protocol/
/debug/
/docs/
/references/
/tests/
/tools/

# AI assistant memory files — local-only, hidden from the remote (owner request)
/CLAUDE.md
/src/CLAUDE.md
